<img src="pix/mememe05.png" alt="" id="me05" class="incremental" />
</p>
</div>

<div class="slide">
<h1>Ways To Cross-Breed and Mutate</h1>
<ul class="incremental">
<li>Cross XFN with VoteLinks<ul><li>What do my friends like/dislike? (or, what do Jeffrey Zeldman's friends like/dislike?)</li></ul></li>
<li>Cross XFN with hCalendar<ul><li>What are my friends up to in the next few weeks?</li></ul></li>
<li>Cross VoteLinks with license annotation<ul><li>What are the most liked/disliked licenses?</li></ul></li>
<li>Cross hCalendar with a music-categorization system<ul><li>When are some upcoming shows by klezmer bands?</li></ul></li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
<h1>A More Immediate Example</h1>
<ul>
<li>Suppose the SXSW Web site used hCalendar to semantically annotate the conference schedules</li>
<li>Using an hCalendar-to-iCalendar (<a href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2445.txt" rel="external">RFC2445</a>) translation script, it would be possible to subscribe to those schedules
<ul><li>...in <a href="http://www.apple.com/ical/" rel="external">iCal</a> or any other calendar program that understands the iCalendar format</li>
<li>The translation script would be needed only until a calendar program was updated to understand the hCalendar microformat</li>
</ul>
</li><li class="incremental">Bingo!  Local copies of the Interactive conference schedule, or the band performance schedule, or the movie schedule, or the whole shootin' Platinum-level match...</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
<h1>Next Steps</h1>
<ul>
<li>Engines are starting to recognize certain <code>rel</code> values; this needs to be expanded to capture all values</li>
<li>For services that have them, API calls to link relation values should be available</li>
<li>Scripts to convert from microformats to RFC formats (and back)</li>
<li>Collections of links to microformatted pages</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
<h1>In Summary</h1>
<ul>
<li>Microformats designed to add semantic information allow quick, evolutionary enrichment of the Web</li>
<li>Anyone can do this; there's no fee to join and almost no barrier to entry</li>
<li>As more microformats emerge, it will be possible to cross-pollinate and get truly human-centric results</li>
<li>Semantics are already starting to emerge and spread</li>
<li>The limits are only what problems we can find to solve, and how creative we are in solving them</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="slide">
